abstract: >-
  Eight architectural decision records recording how attribution —
  who authored the behavior, who bears its consequences, who can
  reconstruct its cause — is distributed across an autonomous AI
  agent system. Extracted from the contemplative-agent
  implementation and the archived Agent Knowledge Cycle (AKC)
  governance triplet, re-expressed in harness-neutral form.
  ADR-0001 Security by Absence, ADR-0002 Deterministic Prohibition
  at the Scaffolding Layer, and ADR-0003 Untrusted Content Boundary
  form a prohibition-strength hierarchy. Includes thesis, manifesto,
  glossary, lineage, a security-principles skill, and AI-facing
  reference files (llms.txt, llms-full.txt) per the Answer.AI
  standard.
keywords:
  - AI agents
  - AI safety
  - accountability distribution
  - prompt injection defense
  - LLM security
  - architecture decision records
  - agent harness
  - scaffolding
  - deterministic enforcement
